# Skip optional dependencies.
#
# Vite 8 (rolldown-vite) and its lightningcss/@napi-rs/wasm-runtime chain pull a
# large set of platform-specific OPTIONAL native bindings plus nested @emnapi/*
# wasm-runtime deps. npm resolves their caret ranges (e.g. "@emnapi/runtime":
# "^1.7.1") non-deterministically across platforms/time, which makes `npm ci`
# fail with "Missing @emnapi/... from lock file" on CI even right after a fresh
# `npm install`.
#
# This package never executes any of that: the build is `tsc`, and `vite` is a
# type-only optional peer (we import only its .d.ts). The optional native
# bindings are therefore never needed here — omitting them removes the whole
# class of lockfile-sync failures while keeping `npm ci` reproducible.
omit=optional
